{"lemma":"دَفَّ","slug":"دَفَّ","root":"د.ف.ف","root_slug":"د-ف-ف","root_link":"/words/roots/د-ف-ف","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n12668"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%81%D9%8E%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to flap the wings (of a bird)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"side, lateral surface"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tambourine"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"A more primitive form of دَفَعَ (dafaʕa, “to push, to propel”), and its resultant noun, already formed before Arabic, though Aramaic דפא / ܕܦܐ (dappā, “board”) is believed to derive from Sumerian 𒁳 (DAB, “board”) / 𒁾 (DUB, “board”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n12668","headword_ar":"دَفَّ","root":"df","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Msb, K, &c.,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M, TA,) or"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, [but this is a deviation from a general rule, and is probably a mistake,]) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafiyfN","text_ar":"دَفِيفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T, S, M, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daf~N","text_ar":"دَفٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Adf~","text_ar":"ادفّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Ibn-' Abbád, M, Msb, K;) said of a bird, (Lth, T, S, &c.,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It beat its sides"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daf~ayohi","text_ar":"دَفَّيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e., Msb,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janobayohi","text_ar":"جَنْبَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", M, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with its wings:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb:) this is what is meant by the following explanation: (Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it moved"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flapped"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its wings"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for its flight,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as the pigeon"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it went"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flew"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"along a little above the ground:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it moved"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flapped"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its wings, with its feet upon the ground,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flying, and then rose;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T;) and in like manner ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafodafa","text_ar":"دَفْدَفَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Astdf~","text_ar":"استدفّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) [or]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"df~","text_ar":"دفّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Adf~","text_ar":"ادفّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a bird)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went along quickly, with its feet upon the ground, and then raised itself flying."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuw^okalu maA daf~a walaA uw^okalu maA","text_ar":"يُوْكَلُ مَا دَفَّ وَلَا ُوْكَلُ مَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Saf~a","text_ar":"صَفَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, * TA,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What moves"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flaps"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its wings"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in flying"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as the pigeon"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may be eaten; but"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what skims along without flapping,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as vultures"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and hawks and the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may not be eaten."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA.) [But]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daf~a","text_ar":"دَفَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", said of an eagle, signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It approached,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was near to, the ground in its flying."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) ―         -b2-  And,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daf~a","text_ar":"دَفَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafiyfN","text_ar":"دَفِيفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daf~N","text_ar":"دَفٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(said of a camel, K, TA, and of a bird, TA, or of a party of men, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went a gentle pace;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafodafa","text_ar":"دَفْدَفَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAar, TA.) Dhu-r-Rummeh uses it metaphorically in relation to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~abaraAni","text_ar":"الدَّبَرَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the asterism of the Hyades, or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"α","text_ar":"α","orth_type":"plain"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Taurus], describing"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alv~uray~aA","text_ar":"الثُّرَيَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the Pleiades]; saying,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"yadif~u EalaYA=vaArihaA dabaraAnuhaA\n                      \n                     \n                        falaA huwa masobuwqN walaA huwa yaloHaqu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Their Debarán goes along gently near after them, so that it is not outstripped, nor does it overtake"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.) [And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tadaAf~a","text_ar":"تَدَافَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to ISd, seems to signify nearly the same: for it is immediately added in the M,] in the saying,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A_ilayoka A^a$okuw ma$oyahaA tadaAfiyaA\n                      \n                     \n                        ma$oYa AlEajuwzi tanoqulu AlA^avaAfiyaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. complaining, to God, of the slowness of his she-camel, as though meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"To Thee I complain of her pressing on slowly and laboriously, like the gait of the old woman removing the three stones for the support of the cooking-pot"},{"kind":"text","text":"], the poet means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tadaAfufFA","text_ar":"تَدَافُفًا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M. [But I rather think that the meaning here intended is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"going along with an inclining from side to side;"},{"kind":"text","text":"perhaps from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daf~N","text_ar":"دَفٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying the “ side. ” See also 6 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dfw","text_ar":"دفو"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljayo$u yadif~uwna naHowa AlEaduw~i","text_ar":"الجَيْشُ يَدِفُّونَ نَحْوَ العَدُوِّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The troops go gently,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leisurely, towards the enemy."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daf~ato EalayonaA mino baniY fulaAnK","text_ar":"دَفَّتْ عَلَيْنَا مِنْ بَنِى فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAf~apN","text_ar":"دَافَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A company coming gently,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leisurely, of the sons of such a one, so came to us"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina AlA^aEoraAbi","text_ar":"مِنَ الاَعْرَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daf~ato Ealayohimo daAf~apN","text_ar":"دَفَّتْ عَلَيْهِمْ دَافَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A company of Arabs of the desert journeying leisurely in search of herbage and sustenance"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"came to them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Z, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo qawomN yadif~uwna","text_ar":"هُمْ قَوْمٌ يَدِفُّونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafiyfN","text_ar":"دَفِيفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They are a party journeying together not a hard pace."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, T.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daf~a EalaY wajohi AlA^aroDi","text_ar":"دَفَّ عَلَى وَجْهِ الاَرْضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, T, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daf~N","text_ar":"دَفٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went lightly upon the ground;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*af~a","text_ar":"ذَفَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same. (IAar, T.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafiyfN","text_ar":"دَفِيفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies The act of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"running."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daf~uwA","text_ar":"دَفُّوا"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", [app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They journeyed to a region of green herbage and waters in consequence of drought:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAf~apN","text_ar":"دَافَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and hence,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they had rain after experiencing drought."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b4-  See also 10, in two places.       -A2-  See also 3.       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daf~a Al$~aYo'a","text_ar":"دَفَّ الشَّىْءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (TK,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daf~N","text_ar":"دَفٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sgh, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He uprooted the thing; extirpated it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sgh, K.)"}],"source_refs":["T","M","TA","Lth","S","Msb","K","IAar","TK","Sgh"]}]}}